    <example xml:id="sample-GT4"><title>GT4</title>
<statement>
    <p>
Explain how to find a basis for the eigenspace associated to the eigenvalue <m>3</m> in the matrix <me>\left[\begin{array}{ccc} -7 &amp; -8 &amp; 2 \\ 8 &amp; 9 &amp; -1 \\ \frac{13}{2} &amp; 5 &amp; 2 \end{array}\right].</me>
    </p>
</statement>
<solution>
    <p>
The eigenspace associated to <m>3</m> is the kernel of <m>A-3I</m>, so we compute
<me>\RREF(A-3I) = \RREF \left[\begin{array}{ccc} -7-3 &amp; -8 &amp; 2 \\ 8 &amp; 9-3 &amp; -1 \\ \frac{13}{2} &amp; 5 &amp; 2-3 \end{array}\right] =
</me><me>\RREF \left[\begin{array}{ccc} -10 &amp; -8 &amp; 2 \\ 8 &amp; 6 &amp; -1 \\ \frac{13}{2} &amp; 5 &amp; -1 \end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{ccc} 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 \\ 0 &amp; 1 &amp; -\frac{3}{2} \\ 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \end{array}\right].</me>
Thus we see the kernel is <me>\setBuilder{\left[\begin{array}{c} -a \\ \frac{3}{2} a \\ a \end{array}\right]}{a \in \IR}</me>
which has a basis of <m>\left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c} -1 \\ \frac{3}{2} \\ 1 \end{array}\right] \right\}</m>.
    </p>
</solution>
</example>